ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: 24-26 good and true lectures on Hatcher, with equally well-guided assignments.
The course requires a lot of work; if one can put that time in, then one will learn topology.
Very interesting and a bit difficult.

The class could accurately be described as "Hatcher part 1." The material is important, and composes the topology qualifying exam, so the class is a must-take unless one knows all the material already.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a substantive understanding of Hatcher 0-3 now, and did not before. It has not yet contributed to my research, which is broadly unrelated.
It help me appreciate many interesting topics in the field and understand important ideas and concepts.
